[[File:God of Taion.png|thumb|right|170px|Taion Shin]] '''Taion Shin''' (太陰神, たいおんじん) is one of the {{ill|Eight Guardian Deities|ja|八将神|1=Eight Directional Deities|12=draft|12=draft}} in {{ill|Onmyōdō|ja|陰陽道|12=draft|12=draft}} and also one of the {{ill|Twelve Heavenly Generals|ja|十二天将|1=Twelve Heavenly Generals (Taoism)|lt=Twelve Heavenly Generals|qq= (Taoism)|12=draft|12=draft}}. In various calendar texts, it may also be written as "だいおん" or "太おん." Additionally, it may be referred to as "大陰," "大陰神," or "太陰," read as "たいいん" or "だいおん." However, it is distinct from the term "太陰" (tai'in), which refers to the {{ill|Moon|ja|月|12=draft|12=draft}}.
Taion Shin is the consort of {{ill|Taisai Shin|ja|太歳神|1=Taisai Shin|12=draft|12=draft}} (the deity associated with {{ill|Jupiter|ja|木星|12=draft|12=draft}}) and represents one of the Eight Guardian Deities. In {{ill|Buddhism|ja|仏教|12=draft|12=draft}}, her {{ill|honji|ja|本地仏|12=draft|12=draft}} is {{ill|Shō Kannon Bosatsu|ja|聖観音菩薩|12=draft|12=draft}}.
As the spirit of {{ill|Saturn|ja|土星|12=draft|12=draft}} (鎮星), Taion Shin embodies the element of {{ill|Earth (Wu Xing)|ja|土|12=draft|12=draft}} (陰). Her nature contrasts with the masculine quality of "陽," and she harbors jealousy toward activities related to feminine matters. Consequently, actions concerning women, such as marriages and childbirth, in the direction of her presence are considered inauspicious. However, endeavors related to {{ill|learning|ja|学問|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|arts|ja|芸術|12=draft|12=draft}} are deemed auspicious.
== Taion Shin's Position == Taion Shin is positioned three directions clockwise from her consort, Taisai Shin.
